Name: tibial neuropathy
Definition: A leprosy that is an early form of the disease which causes one to a few hypopigmented or erythematous macules.

Name: radial neuropathy

Name: femoral neuropathy
Definition: A mononeuropathy that is characterized by a loss of movement or sensation in parts of the legs due to damage to the femoral nerve.

Name: peroneal neuropathy
